SIMPLE: hallucinate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hallucinate
<hw>Hal*lu"ci*nate</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧l*l⟦umac⟧"s⟦icr⟧*n⟦amac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>hallucinatus</ets>,
<ets>alucinatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>hallucinari</ets>,
<ets>alucinari</ets>, to wander in mind, talk idly, dream.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To wander; to go astray; to err; to blunder; -- used of
mental processes.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>To perceive a
non-existent object or phenomenon; to believe that one is experiencing
something which in reality does not exist; to experience a
hallucination{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hallucinate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: hallucinate
<hw>hal*lu"ci*nate</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧l*l⟦umac⟧"s⟦icr⟧*n⟦amac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To experience (something nonexistent) as an
hallucination{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hallucinating</ent>⟦br⟧
